messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path:
  /printshops/{printShopID}/employees

- All HTTP methods acceptable:
  No

- HEAD:
  No

- POST:
  Yes

- OPTIONS:
  No

- TRACE:
  No

- GET:
  Yes

- PUT:
  Yes

- DELETE:
  No

- PATCH:
  No

Explanation:
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping on ManagerController, so the method-level paths are used verbatim.
- The methods mapped to /printshops/{printShopID}/employees in the source are:
  - getEmployees(...) annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{printShopID}/employees", method = RequestMethod.GET) → GET is allowed.
  - addEmployee(...) annotated with ... method = RequestMethod.POST → POST is allowed.
  - editEmployee(...) annotated with ... method = RequestMethod.PUT → PUT is allowed.
  (See the corresponding @RequestMapping annotations in ManagerController.java.)
- DELETE is not allowed on /printshops/{printShopID}/employees because the deleteEmployee(...) handler is mapped to /printshops/{printShopID}/employees/{employeeID} (different path).
- HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, and PATCH are not present as explicit @RequestMapping methods for this path in the code, so they are considered not acceptable based strictly on the source annotations.
